<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="30" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1944,2008]" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1944,1970]" pageId="1" pageNumber="30">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Gonostyle directed laterally on basal thirds and then strongly curved apically, bifid at apex, main apical branch with four elongated spines. Aedeagus trifid at base.
</paragraph>
